[Patient] What foods should I eat to help with my heart failure?
[Educator] Focus on fruits, veggies, whole grains, and lean proteins for a healthy heart.
[Patient] I can't afford expensive food. Any tips for eating healthy on a budget?
[Educator] Buy in bulk, shop for seasonal produce, and cook at home to save money on groceries.
[Patient] I love my traditional foods. Can I still eat them while managing heart failure?
[Educator] You can modify your favorite dishes to be heart-healthy by using less salt and oil.
[Patient] Where can I find affordable and nutritious food options in my neighborhood?
[Educator] Check out local food banks, farmer's markets, and community gardens for fresh and affordable groceries.
[Patient] How can I track if my diet is helping my heart failure symptoms?
[Educator] Monitor your weight, blood pressure, and symptoms regularly to see how your diet affects you.